## Non-negotiable rules

- **Log every meaningful discovery** in [logbook/LOG.md](logbook/LOG.md) (use
  [logbook/TEMPLATE.md](logbook/TEMPLATE.md)) — not every conversation step. A LOG
  entry is for things worth remembering across sessions: {{#if use_gates}}a gate
  changing state, {{/if}}an artifact arriving, a hands-on result, a dead end that
  rules something out. Mid-investigation reasoning and intermediate findings stay
  in the conversation until they settle. When in doubt, batch: one entry per real
  checkpoint, written when the picture is clear. Don't edit tracking files every
  turn.
{{#if use_gates}}
- **Respect the gates.** Do not act past a gate whose condition isn't met. A HARD
  gate can terminate the project — don't pretend around it.
{{/if}}
{{rules_block}}
{{#if has_artifacts}}
- **Every artifact gets a manifest** ([artifacts/manifests/](artifacts/manifests/)),
  a sha256, and a provenance note. {{#if private_archive}}The files themselves
  **are committed** (private archive repo) — only reproducible blobs are
  git-ignored. {{/if}}Treat downloaded binaries as untrusted; run only in a
  disposable environment.
{{/if}}

{{#if private_archive}}
## Privacy

**Always-private archive repo.** It commits scarce artifacts, evidence, and all
docs — intentionally, as the durable backup. Only reproducible blobs are
git-ignored. **Never push to a shared or public remote.** See
[docs/PRIVACY.md](docs/PRIVACY.md).
{{/if}}

## Git

Per global prefs: stage when ready, **don't commit unprompted** — wait for the
user. Conventional Commits.

## Conventions

- Dates absolute (`YYYY-MM-DD`).
- Record error strings, identifiers, and version numbers **verbatim** — they're
  how threads/docs get searched and how mis-identification gets caught.
{{#if has_artifacts}}- New artifact → manifest from [artifacts/manifests/_TEMPLATE.md](artifacts/manifests/_TEMPLATE.md) + a row in `INDEX.md`.
{{/if}}- New hands-on session → optional `logbook/sessions/<date>-<topic>.md`, summarized
  back into `LOG.md`.
